{{Infobox Noble | Name = Takei-Otake-no-Mikoto (武五百建命) | image = | image Size = | Caption = | Era = {{ill|Ancient Japan|ja|上古|12=draft|12=draft}}・{{ill|Kofun period|ja|古墳時代|12=draft|12=draft}} | Birth = Unknown | Death = Unknown | Renamed = | Posthumous Name = | Deity Name = | Dharma Name = | Burial Site = Believed to be {{ill|Mori Shōgunzuka Kofun|ja|森将軍塚古墳|12=draft|12=draft}}<ref name="jiten">[http://www.nihonjiten.com/data/263245.html Kuno Kokuzō (Shinano)] - Nihon Jiten (Accessed July 6, 2018, 4:29 AM [[Japan Standard Time|JST]])</ref> | Rank = First {{ill|Kuno Kokuzō|ja|科野国造|1=Shina no Kuni no Miyatsuko|12=draft|12=draft}}<ref>“{{ill|Kokuzō Honki|ja|国造本紀|12=draft|12=draft}}” Kuno Kokuzō entry.</ref> | Master = {{ill|Emperor Sujin|ja|崇神天皇|12=draft|12=draft}} | Clan = {{ill|Ō Clan|ja|多氏|1=Ō clan|12=draft|12=draft}} (ancestor of the {{ill|Shinano Clan|ja|科野君|12=draft|12=draft}}, {{ill|Kanasashi Clan|ja|金刺舎人直|12=draft|12=draft}}, {{ill|Tada Clan|ja|他田舎人直|12=draft|12=draft}}, etc.) | Parents = | Siblings = | Wife = | Children = | Notable Facts = }} '''Takei-Otake-no-Mikoto''' (武五百建命, also written as たけいおたけのみこと, たけいおたつのみこと, [[birth and death dates unknown]]) was a [[Kofun period]] [[gōzoku]] (local noble) and the first '''{{ill|Kuno Kokuzō|ja|科野国造|1=Shina no Kuni no Miyatsuko|12=draft|12=draft}}'''. In the "{{ill|Kokuzō Honki|ja|国造本紀|12=draft|12=draft}}" section of the {{ill|Sendai Kuji Hongi|ja|先代旧事本紀|12=draft|12=draft}}, he is referred to as '''Tatei-Otake-no-Mikoto'''.
== Overview ==
According to the "{{ill|Kokuzō Honki|ja|国造本紀|12=draft|12=draft}}" section of the {{ill|Sendai Kuji Hongi|ja|先代旧事本紀|12=draft|12=draft}}, Takei-Otake-no-Mikoto was the grandson of {{ill|Kamuyaimimi|ja|神八井耳命|12=draft|12=draft}} and was appointed as the first '''{{ill|Kuno Kokuzō|ja|科野国造|1=Shina no Kuni no Miyatsuko|12=draft|12=draft}}''' during the reign of {{ill|Emperor Sujin|ja|崇神天皇|12=draft|12=draft}}. Tradition holds that he founded the {{ill|Shinano Ōmiyasha|ja|科野大宮社|12=draft|12=draft}}.
== Genealogy ==
Takei-Otake-no-Mikoto is said to be the grandson of {{ill|Kamuyaimimi|ja|神八井耳命|12=draft|12=draft}}<ref>“{{ill|Sendai Kuji Hongi|ja|先代旧事本紀|12=draft|12=draft}},” Kokuzō Honki, Kuno Kokuzō entry.</ref>.
== Shrines Enshrining Him ==
*{{ill|Futago Shrine (Ueda City)|ja|二子神社 (上田市)|12=draft|12=draft}} ({{ill|Nagano Prefecture|ja|長野県|12=draft|12=draft}}, {{ill|Ueda City|ja|上田市|12=draft|12=draft}}) *{{ill|Susuki Mizugami Shrine (Chikuma City)|ja|須須岐水神社 (千曲市)|12=draft|12=draft}}, within its grounds, the Iwai Shrine (Nagano Prefecture, {{ill|Chikuma City|ja|千曲市|12=draft|12=draft}}, Yashiro) *{{ill|Karasaki Shrine (Chikuma City)|ja|唐崎神社 (千曲市)|12=draft|12=draft}} (Nagano Prefecture, Chikuma City, Amamiya)
== Notes == {{Reflist}} == See Also == *[[Kuni no miyatsuko]] *{{ill|List of People Before the Asuka Period|ja|飛鳥時代以前の人物一覧|12=draft|12=draft}}
